What you need to know:

Young farmers form the majority of people trading online. According to our recent survey, those aged 18-34 years comprise 50 percent of users.All farm products are sold online, but the bulk is horticultural crops, livestock and livestock products and farm equipment.The younger generation is using the platforms more because digital technologies have been widely adopted by them.The government has played its part in providing the relevant infrastructure such as ensuring internet connectivity even to some of the remote areas.